er]] || English || 1961 || 10 million<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/pmextra/dec99/13/heller.htm|title='Catch-22' Author Joseph Heller Dies|date=1999-12-13|accessdate=2009-08-31|publisher=Washingtonpost.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120117100525/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/pmextra/dec99/13/heller.htm|archivedate=2012-01-17}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[The Stranger (Camus novel)|The Stranger]]'' (''L'\u00c9tranger'')|| [[Albert Camus]] || French || 1942 || 10 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rusoffagency.com/authors/kaplan_a/looking/looking_for_the_stranger.htm|title=Looking for the Stranger|website=rusoffagency.com|access-date=2017-01-29|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114002627/http://rusoffagency.com/authors/kaplan_a/looking/looking_for_the_stranger.htm|archivedate=2016-11-14}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Eye of the Needle (novel)|Eye of the Needle]]'' || [[Ken Follett]] || English || 1978 || 10 million<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=xkGlUNW09eEC&pg=PA44&dq=%22eye+of+the+needle%22+%2210+million+copies%22&ei=lI70R7TpJYWwzgSGgvnIAQ&sig=_3n61rMQugtQjVN8U--Wd2Cvw7g Carlos Ramet in ''Ken Follett: The Transformation of a Writer''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170326162045/https://books.google.com/books?id=xkGlUNW09eEC&pg=PA44&dq=%22eye+of+the+needle%22+%2210+million+copies%22&ei=lI70R7TpJYWwzgSGgvnIAQ&sig=_3n61rMQugtQjVN8U--Wd2Cvw7g |date=2017-03-26 }} page 44 on Ken Follett: \"The first two editions alone sold over 10 million copies worldwide\" (1999)</ref>\n|-\n|''[[The Lovely Bones]]'' || [[Alice Sebold]] || English || 2002 || 10 million<ref>[http://tvnz.co.nz/view/page/411319/1098660 TVNZ] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090925100537/http://tvnz.co.nz/view/page/411319/1098660|date=2009-09-25}} on ''The Lovely Bones'': \"Published in 2002, Lovely Bones is the second novel by Alice Sebold, and has sold over 10 million copies worldwide, remaining on the New